# Local Loop Discipline

Do not add slow checks, watchers, prebuild hooks, generated churn, or source-mutating build steps unless they replace something or protect a proven high-risk invariant.

- Prefer explicit commands for expensive checks; do not start dev servers/watchers.
- If a check is duplicated in CI/build/prebuild, call it out and avoid adding another layer.
- For small docs/rule/test-only changes, state which full gates are irrelevant and why.
- Automate last: contracts, hydration checks, realtime events, and guardrails should preserve a simplified system, not freeze bloat in place.
